description: The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide is back with its 38th edition and it is packed with all sorts of details from the world of comics, including feature articles on the fabled DC ashcan comics, the Gaines file copies and the history of Star Wars in comics. The Guide remains the most complete listing of comics from the 1500s to the present.

volume.name: The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide

description: The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide, the definitive guide for comic collectors and dealers alike, is back for its 39th edition, including a 70th anniversary look at Batman's first year, an introduction to The Hero Initiative, an amazing roster of new entries in the Overstreet Hall of Fame, and the most extensive pricing from the world of comics! This edition features a choice of two covers - a great modern interpretation of The Avengers #1 by John K. Snyder III and a spot-on recreation of the classic All-Select Comics #1 by Murphy Anderson.

volume.name: The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide

description: Celebrate the landmark 40th edition of the comic collector's Bible! Since 1970, the Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide has been the definitive guide for comic collectors and dealers alike. New collectors and seasoned enthusiasts will find all new insights, features, and data, along with the most comprehensive listing of comics all new entries in the Overstreet Hall of Fame. Acclaimed artist Mark Chiarello (Batman/Houdini: The Devil's Workshop) supplies the Batman cover, while Eisner Award-winning artist Darwyn Cooke (DC: The New Frontier) supplies the Captain America cover.

volume.name: The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide

description: Entering its fifth decade as the preeminent source of comic book pricing information, The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide has been the definitive guide for collectors and dealers alike since 1970. In addition to a choice of covers - Thor (by signature Mighty Thor artist, Walter Simonson!) or Supergirl/Batgirl (by Power Girl superstar Amanda Conner!), this 41st edition includes all the new insights, features, and data, along with the most comprehensive listing of comics and all-new entries in the Overstreet Hall of Fame. Perfect for both new collectors and seasoned enthusiasts. Available in Softcover and Hardcover editions of both cover designs.

volume.name: The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide

description: There's a good reason The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide has been the definitive guide for collectors and dealers alike since 1970. In addition to being the preeminent source of comic book pricing information, it features a ton of other data as well. The 42nd edition includes all new insights and features and along with the most comprehensive listing of comics, all new entries in the Overstreet Hall of Fame, and more. This edition offers a choice of covers: A vibrant Catwoman caught in the act by signature artist Adam Hughes, or a stunning re-creation of John Buscema's Avengers #58 cover by superstar painter Joe Jusko. Either version is perfect for both new collectors and seasoned enthusiasts alike, and they're both available in softcover and hardcover editions.

volume.name: The Overstreet Comic Book Price Guide

It's no secret that Vertigo has been on the front lines of graphic ﬁction for twenty years and counting. This preview book gives you a first look at the projects that will DEFY your expectations in 2013 including Neil Gaiman's return to The Sandman, Scott Snyder and Sean Murphy's THE WAKE, Jeff Lemire's TRILLIUM, Brian Azzarello and Eduardo Risso's 100 BULLETS: BROTHER LONO, plus much, much more. You won't want to miss a millisecond as we introduce the new blood and bravado that will DEFY the rules and deﬁne the next era of Vertigo.

When one little boy finds the courage to stand up to this alien invader, it just might be enough to inspire the return of the world’s greatest superhero… CAPTAIN ULTIMATE!

description:
JUNK ONE is a digital collection of artwork by New York Times Best Selling artist and multiple Eisner Award winner, Skottie Young.

The print version of JUNK ONE had a print run of 1000 copies and sold out. This is your chance to enjoy the 104 page art book now that it is out of print.

This book is filled with everything you could want out of an art book. Sketches, doodles, experiments, paintings, concepts, digital drawing, success, failures, and everything in between. JUNK ONE gives you a look at the personal work of a fan favorite comic book artist and cartoonist.

This is a digital book of THE ADVENTURES OF BERNARD THE WORLD DESTROYER. You read this PDF on any of your digital readers such as iPhone, iPad, and many others.

Bernard comes to Earth to study our animals, movies, past times, and our celebrities...if you can call them that. The outlook does not look good for our planet.

The Adventures Of Bernard The World Destroyer is a collection of the online daily comic written and illustrated by Skottie Young (Artist of New York Times Best Selling multiple Eisner Award winning Wonderful Wizard of Oz).

Plus, exclusive bonus art by artists Tom Fowler, Mike Norton, Nic Klein, Rafael Albuquerque, Darren Rawls, Chris Samnee, Francis Vallejo, Ramon Perez and Mike Hawthorne.
